'''Capoeiras''' (''Scrubs'') is a city located in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. Located at 252.7&nbsp;km away from [[Recife]], capital of the state of Pernambuco. Has an estimated ([[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|Ibge 2009]]) population of 19.936 inhabitants.
==Geography== * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste|Agreste Pernambucano]] * Boundaries - [[São Bento do Una]] ('''N'''); [[Garanhuns]] ('''S'''); [[Jucati]] ('''E'''); [[Pesqueira, Pernambuco|Pesqueira]] and [[Caetés, Pernambuco|Caetés]] ('''W'''). * Area - 335.26&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 888 m * Hydrography - [[Mundaú River|Mundaú]] and [[Una River (Pernambuco)|Una rivers]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[Hiperxerófila]] * Climate - [[Semi arid]] * Annual average temperature - 20.4 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 252.7&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Capoeiras''' are based in commerce and [[agribusiness]], especially [[tomato]]es, [[bean]]s, [[manioc]], [[maize|corn]]; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]], [[pig]]s, [[sheep]] and [[poultry]].
